    ],
    "answer": null,
    "explanation": "<p>$$ \\text {  } \\begin{aligned}Let\\,\\, P(x) & =\\left(1+x-2 x^2\\right)^6 \\\\ & =1+a_1 x+a_2 x^2+\\ldots a_{12} x^{12} \\end{aligned} $$</p>\n<p>We need fo find $a_2+a_4+a_6+\\ldots+a_{12}$.</p>\n<p>We know that the sum of coefficients of even powers is $\\frac{P(1)+P(-1)}{2}$</p>\n<p>$$ \\begin{aligned} P(1) & =\\left(1+1-2(1)^2\\right)^6=(0)^6=0 \\\\ P(-1) & =\\left(1+(-1)-2(-1)^2\\right)^6 \\\\ & =(-2)^6=64 \\end{aligned} $$</p>\n<p>Sum of coefficients of even powers $=\\frac{0+64}{2}=32$</p>\n<p>This sum includes $a_0$.</p>\n<p>From the given expansion, the constant term</p>\n<p>$$ a_0=P(0)=(1+0-0)^6=1 $$</p>\n<p>So, $\\quad a_0+a_2+a_4+\\ldots+a_{12}=32$</p>\n<p>Therefore, $a_2+a_4+a_6+\\ldots+a_{12}=32-a_0$</p>\n<p>$$ =32-1=31 $$</p>",
